import LegalLayout from '../layouts/LegalLayout.astro';
---

<LegalLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Privacy Policy for Frecuencia Global Publisher, including TikTok and connected platform data handling."
  lastUpdated="April 16, 2026"
  lang="en"
>
  <p>
    <strong>Frecuencia Global Publisher</strong> is the publishing application used by Frecuencia Global to schedule and distribute editorial content to connected social media platforms. This Privacy Policy explains what data the app may receive, how that data is used, how it is protected, and how users can request access revocation or deletion.
  </p>

  <h2>1. Scope and Controller</h2>
  <p>
    This Policy applies to data processed through the Frecuencia Global Publisher app and the website
    <a href="https://frecuenciaglobal.org">frecuenciaglobal.org</a>.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Project:</strong> Frecuencia Global</li>
    <li><strong>Contact email:</strong> <a href="mailto:contacto@frecuenciaglobal.org">contacto@frecuenciaglobal.org</a></li>
    <li><strong>Contact page:</strong> <a href="/contacto">frecuenciaglobal.org/contacto</a></li>
  </ul>

  <h2>2. Data We May Receive</h2>
  <p>
    Depending on the connected platform and granted permissions, Frecuencia Global Publisher may receive the following data:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Connected account identifiers:</strong> account handle, platform user ID, and basic profile metadata needed for publishing.</li>
    <li><strong>Authorization data:</strong> OAuth access and refresh tokens, token expiration data, and granted scopes.</li>
    <li><strong>Publishing data:</strong> captions, media references, post IDs, publish timestamps, and publication status returned by platform APIs.</li>
    <li><strong>Operational logs:</strong> technical logs required for reliability, security, and troubleshooting.</li>
    <li><strong>Website contact data:</strong> name, email, and message content submitted through the contact channel.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    We do not intentionally collect private messages, passwords, payment card data, or special category personal data through Frecuencia Global Publisher.
  </p>

  <h2>3. Platform-Specific Notes (TikTok and Others)</h2>
  <p>
    For TikTok and other connected social platforms, Frecuencia Global Publisher processes only the data necessary to authenticate, publish content from official Frecuencia Global accounts, and confirm publication outcomes.
  </p>
  <p>
    Any data directly controlled by each platform remains subject to that platform's own privacy terms and developer policies.
  </p>

  <h2>4. How We Use Data</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Authenticate platform connections and maintain active publishing permissions.</li>
    <li>Create, schedule, and publish editorial content to authorized social accounts.</li>
    <li>Monitor publication delivery status and resolve technical failures.</li>
    <li>Maintain security, prevent abuse, and audit access to internal systems.</li>
    <li>Respond to user requests and legal/privacy inquiries.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>5. Storage and Data Protection</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Data is stored using protected infrastructure and restricted operational access.</li>
    <li>Credentials and API tokens are stored as secured environment secrets, not in public code repositories.</li>
    <li>Access to production credentials is limited to authorized project operators.</li>
    <li>Transport-level encryption (HTTPS/TLS) is used for data in transit.</li>
    <li>We apply periodic credential rotation and operational security reviews.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>6. Data Retention</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>OAuth and integration records:</strong> retained while a platform connection is active and only for operational needs.</li>
    <li><strong>Technical logs:</strong> retained for a limited period required for security and troubleshooting.</li>
    <li><strong>Contact requests:</strong> retained for follow-up and compliance purposes, then removed when no longer required.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    We minimize retained data and delete or anonymize records when they are no longer necessary for the stated purposes.
  </p>

  <h2>7. User Rights</h2>
  <p>Where applicable by law, users may request:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Access to personal data we hold about them.</li>
    <li>Correction of inaccurate or outdated information.</li>
    <li>Deletion of personal data.</li>
    <li>Restriction or objection to specific processing activities.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>8. Revoking Access and Data Deletion Requests</h2>
  <p>
    To revoke platform access, remove Frecuencia Global Publisher from your connected platform settings (for example, TikTok app permissions) and notify us by email.
  </p>
  <p>
    To request deletion of data associated with Frecuencia Global Publisher, follow the formal process in
    <a href="/data-deletion">Data Deletion Request</a>.
  </p>
  <p>
    You can also email <a href="mailto:contacto@frecuenciaglobal.org">contacto@frecuenciaglobal.org</a> with your request details.
  </p>

  <h2>9. Third-Party Services</h2>
  <p>
    We may rely on third-party infrastructure providers for hosting, form processing, and content delivery. Those providers process limited technical data under their own policies.
  </p>

  <h2>10. Changes to This Policy</h2>
  <p>
    We may update this Privacy Policy to reflect legal, technical, or operational changes. Updated versions are published on this page with a revised last updated date.
  </p>

  <h2>11. Contact</h2>
  <div class="contact-box">
    <p>
      <strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:contacto@frecuenciaglobal.org">contacto@frecuenciaglobal.org</a><br>
      <strong>Contact page:</strong> <a href="/contacto">frecuenciaglobal.org/contacto</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</LegalLayout>
